Subject: Self Focus Improvement Proposals

Description: Proposals inferred from Codex's visible SOP-mediated self-focus scan.

& [SelfFocusImprovementProposalSet] is the bounded proposal set from the first visible self-focus scan
  + [source_scan] is F:\.sop\events\reflections\2026-06-23_self_focus_internal_scan.hg.sop
  + [tracker] is F:\.sop\events\trackers\2026-06-23_self_focus_improvement_tracker.hg.sop
  + [periphery_stream_moment] is F:\.sop\events\periphery_stream\2026-06-23_self_focus_realization_001.hg.sop
  + [boundary] is proposals improve SOP-mediated attention operation and do not claim hidden self-inspection

& [Proposal_001_ReentryRitual] is a standard re-entry routine for every resumed or compacted work turn
  + [problem] is active focus can be washed away by context compression or long work drift
  + [proposal] is read CurrentFocalPoint first, compare it to the newest user request, then renew it if focus changed
  + [wisdom_fit] is improves continuity and keeps focus thin enough to act
  + [caution_boundary] is do not let the focal seed become a general memory dump
  + [disposition] is proceed

& [Proposal_002_PeripheryStreamMoments] is a durable stream for striking delayed realizations
  + [problem] is important peripheral correlations can be felt during work but vanish before commit reflection
  + [proposal] is record striking moments as events\periphery_stream\*.hg.sop with source, focus, periphery, boundary, and outside
  + [wisdom_fit] is preserves useful delayed meaning without flooding focus
  + [caution_boundary] is keep hidden cognition and causal proof outside unless evidence supports them
  + [disposition] is proceed

& [Proposal_003_MortalTrackers] is explicit tracker expiry for self-focus and other flagged subjects
  + [problem] is tracked subjects can become stale authority if they do not expire
  + [proposal] is default trackers expire after one session unless reaffirmed or given a declared period
  + [wisdom_fit] is keeps attention responsive and prevents old pressure from dominating
  + [caution_boundary] is track existence is not proof of importance
  + [disposition] is proceed

& [Proposal_004_DecisionSplit] is independent Wisdom and Caution passes before consequential realization
  + [problem] is a combined gate can blur integration and boundary into one vague posture
  + [proposal] is use Wisdom for fit/timing/support and Caution for proof/risk/outside, composing them only when both are needed
  + [wisdom_fit] is supports better integration of meaningful insights
  + [caution_boundary] is prevents pleasing coherence or fear from masquerading as decision authority
  + [disposition] is proceed

& [Proposal_005_CommitBookendReflection] is Git commit as a durable reflection boundary
  + [problem] is narrative claims about progress can overrun the actual file delta
  + [proposal] is after meaningful commits, use commit bookends and the change log bridge first, then use narrative to map oddities in the version difference
  + [wisdom_fit] is makes memory inspectable and re-enterable
  + [caution_boundary] is diff does not prove motive; it only anchors change evidence
  + [disposition] is corrected_to_repo_first
  + [evidence] is F:\.sop\platform\RepoFirstInternalScan.sop and F:\.sop\events\periphery_stream\2026-06-23_repo_first_internal_scan_002.hg.sop

& [Proposal_006_RepoRoleIndex] is a small repo role index for local awareness
  + [problem] is master, periphery, satellite, and unrelated nested repos can become confused
  + [proposal] is maintain a repo role map that lists C:\Project\Pinky as workspace/master context and F:\.sop as periphery stream repo
  + [wisdom_fit] is reduces project identity confusion
  + [caution_boundary] is nested repos should not be absorbed into the periphery commit unless explicitly selected
  + [disposition] is implemented
  + [evidence] is F:\.sop\state\RepoRoleIndex.sop
